#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Selecting a gRPC server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Quarkus provides two implementation of the gRPC server: gRPC Java (based on Netty) and Vert.x.\n"
"Both of them support TLS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "One of the advantage of the Vert.x based server is the ability to use a single server to handle HTTP requests and gRPC requests. This is useful if you want to expose both REST and gRPC endpoints on the same port. This is not possible with the gRPC Java server (using a separate server)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "To select the gRPC server implementation, set the `quarkus.grpc.server.use-separate-server` property in your `application.properties` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "We recommend the usage of the Vert.x based gRPC server, as it is more flexible and better integrated in the Quarkus ecosystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "You cannot use both servers at the same time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Performance tuning for large messages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "When working with large gRPC messages, you may need to tune the HTTP/2 flow control window size to achieve optimal throughput."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Unified server mode (Vert.x-based)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "When using the unified server mode (`quarkus.grpc.server.use-separate-server=false`), you can configure the HTTP/2 connection window size:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "The `quarkus.http.http2-connection-window-size` property sets the HTTP/2 connection window size in bytes. The default value is `-1`, which reuses the initial window size setting (typically 64KB). For large messages, increasing this value can significantly improve throughput."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Separate server mode (gRPC Java/Netty-based)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "When using the separate server mode (`quarkus.grpc.server.use-separate-server=true`), you can configure the flow control window using a `ServerBuilderCustomizer`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "The separate server mode provides more direct control over Netty-specific settings but requires a dedicated port for gRPC traffic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Listening on a Random Port"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"If you don't want to specify a port you can set `quarkus.http.port=0` and `quarkus.http.test-port=0` when using Vert.x\n"
"(`quarkus.grpc.server.use-separate-server=false)` or `quarkus.grpc.server.port=0` and `quarkus.grpc.server.test-port=0`\n"
"when using the gRPC server. A random open port will be picked by the OS, and a log message printed in the console."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"To retrieve the real port, use the `io.quarkus.grpc.runtime.GrpcServer` API, which can be injected into the application\n"
"code as a CDI Bean:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Or into any kind of test, either as a field or test parameter:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Selecting gRPC clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"As for the server, Quarkus proposes two alternatives for the gRPC clients: gRPC Java and Vert.x.\n"
"Unlike for the server, you can select the transport for each client:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"While it's not the default, we recommend using the Vert.x based client, as it is more flexible and better integrated in the Quarkus ecosystem.\n"
"It does not change the stubs you can use, as they are generated by the gRPC framework.\n"
"However, it changes the way the client communicates with the server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "Client-side flow control window"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "When working with large messages, you can configure the flow control window for gRPC clients:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/grpc-reference.adoc
msgid "The default flow control window is 1MB. Increasing this value can improve throughput when receiving large messages from the server."
msgstr ""

